<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stole this from Lum the Mad</span><hr size=1> Aye, he seems to be contradicting himself on that point.  Worrying about realism in a fantasy setting.  Heh, this guy sounds like he's working on a degree in Medieval Studies (Heh, amusingly enough my university offers both an undergraduate and graduate program in MS) and getting hung up on historical accuracy (Weapon designs, economics of agrarian societies, etc...)<br>
<br>
The specific areas in the article that I found most interesting and possibly useful to designers were the section on server economies, balance and the general section.  <br>
<br>
Looking at server economies, EQ is not the worst I've seen but certainly far from the best...  Anyone who's spent time /aucing stuff in EC has seen how weird the economy is at times.  Heh, and from what I've seen and heard, the luclin economy is actually one of the healthier ones.  <br>
<br>
I've played on other online RPGs which have implemented concepts like wear on items through use, timed decay, etc..  It's a pain in the ass..  A serious pain..  yeah it helps keep the economy fluid, but it seriously sucks when your uber item of ass kicking has to go in the bin.  Of course there were options for 'repairing' items..  One specific MUD used a timed decay rate (90 days I think) which could be extended by the use of items (Eggs) harvested from an insanely hard dungeon called &quot;The  Catacombs&quot; 100 eggs gave you an extra 30 days.  And after 1000 eggs, you could no longer extend the life of an item.<br>
<br>
Of course that simply shifted the basis of the economy from gp to eggs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    The other thing is that item maintainance is not fun.  It's tedious, it's boring..  Not good things to include in a game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
This sort of issue isn't going to be as big of an issue for your server, since it's not going to be 20,000+ people per server.  That doesn't mean that the problem won't happen, just that inflation will happen a lot more slowly.  With the smaller GM:Population ratio, it's also something that you use a Deus Ex Machina approach to fix <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Heh, images of Monty Python and the big hand coming down out of the sky to squash the folks camping the uber dungeon leap to mind.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, thanks for posting the link..  It was an interesting read..  <p><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=4 COLOR=0000AA><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=58011">Feyatha Stormseeker</a></B></FONT><BR>
