<br>
Most the major items in my game will come via quest, thus easily controlled by simple changing the quest whenever I feel an item has become too common.  Players will quickly learn (I hope) that the NWN world will be dynamic to a much larger extent then EQ could do. <p>Segal
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/umaoudeib.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maoudeib</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 853<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/22/01 10:40:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stole this from Lum the Mad</span><hr size=1> Well, there's also another big limitation.  People running games have the final say on what items they will allow.<br>
<br>
For example, if I design a dungeon for level 10 players with level 10 type of equipment, I'm not going to allow in a 20th level/20 level fighter/mage with a vorpal sword and glowing dragon armor.<br>
<br>
I've been playing Baldur's gate and have noticed this occuring very much.  People attempt to play hacked characters or &quot;twinked&quot; characters and are met with much resistance.<br>
<br>
You can also decide to not allow any outside items in a high level dungeon you created.  The game might start with your characters captured and imprisoned, for example.<br>
<br>
I'm sure their will be areas to trade and purchase items in game. However, it's too easy to fashion items as a dungeon creator.  Too many people will be able to make &quot;Monty Hall&quot; type of dungeons with the best armor and weapons scattered like pebbles on the floor.<br>
<br>
This is all in line with the old D&amp;D of paper and pen. Sure I could put together a sheet of an awesome character with impossible stats and equipment.  But the more incredible the character and his equipment, the less games he will be admitted to without change.<br>
<br>
The main allure of NWN will be investigating new dungeons, which I'm sure will be plentiful over time.  This is something EQ, UO and no other online game can offer...endless new adventures...limited only by the imagination of dungeon creators out there.<br>
 <p>Phantasmist Maob<BR>
Agnostic: Atypical Nonbeliever
Semi-Retired
